At Applux, we value your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines our practices regarding the collection, use, and sharing of your information through our services (referred to collectively as the "Services"). We are dedicated to protecting your privacy in accordance with the terms of this policy.
Compliance with Google API Services
We adhere to the
Google API Services User Data Policy
and observe its Limited Use requirements when using information obtained from Google APIs. The specifics include:
Restricting human access to your data unless we receive your explicit consent.
Prohibiting the use of your data for advertising purposes such as retargeting, personalized, or interest-based ads.
Using the data solely to enhance or provide user-centric features visible in our application.
Allowing data transfer only when necessary to facilitate or improve user-centric features.
Information Sharing with Third Party AI Platform
We value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. In accordance with this policy, we do not share any personal information with third-party AI platforms, with the sole exception of the prompts you input while utilizing AI to create Google Forms. For example, a prompt such as 'User feedback form for a t-shirt brand' may be shared. It is important to note that these prompts are processed in a manner that completely disassociates them from your identity, ensuring that they cannot be linked back to you or any specific individual. Additionally, we implement strict data security measures to protect the integrity and confidentiality of your data.
Information Collection
We gather various types of information, including:
Personal Information:
This includes details like your name & email address which you provide when you register for our Services or interact with us.
Usage Information:
We automatically collect information related to your interactions and usage of our Services, such as log data and device information.
Use of Information
To deliver and manage our Services, including account creation, payment processing, and communications regarding your account.
To customize your experience with our Services, offering tailored content and recommendations.
To improve and innovate our Services by analyzing trends and user behaviors.
To safeguard our rights and property and fulfill our legal responsibilities.
Information Sharing
We might share your information under these circumstances:
With your consent.
With third-party service providers who assist us in operating our Services, such as hosting, payment processing, analytics and customer support.
In response to legal requests or when necessary to protect our rights, property, or the safety of our users and the public.
User Rights and Preferences
You can control how we use and share your information through several options:
“Limit Ad Tracking" on your iOs device in Settings/ Privacy/ Advertising, please find additional information here:
https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT202074
;
“Opt out of Ad Personalization” on your Android device in Settings/ Google/ Ads.
To opt-out of interest based advertising you can also visit:
https://youradchoices.com.
;
Opt-Out of the Location Data Processing
Certain third-party advertising partners may collect precise location data, or street-level location information about you (“Precise Location Data”). Your mobile device may allow you to opt out of the collection of Precise Location Data as further described below.
iOS 11 or later
In order to disable the collection of Precise Location Data on iOS, you may turn Location Services off for the applicable Product via the menu
“Settings > Privacy > Location Services”
. Then select the applicable App and set the “Share My Location” status to “Never”. Please see additional information here:
https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT203033.
Security Measures
We implement appropriate security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no security system is infallible, and we cannot guarantee complete security of your data.
Policy Updates
We may modify this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in legal, technical, or business practices. Should there be a significant modification, we will notify you via email or through a notice on our website.
